caption:
Table 1: MDMA for causal discovery. Conditional densities from a trained MDMA model can be 
used for causal discovery by allowing to test for conditional independence between variables. Both 
on synthetic DAG data and real data from a protein signaling network, MDMA infers the graph 
structure more accurately than a competing method based on quantile regression
